  "text": "## Prometheus Metric Registration Patterns Across Three Major Projects\n\n### Kubernetes (kubernetes/kubernetes)\n\nKubernetes uses a **custom metrics wrapper framework** built on top of the Prometheus client library:\n\n- **Central Registry**: The global registry is defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/legacyregistry/registry.go` which wraps a `metrics.NewKubeRegistry()` and exposes functions like `MustRegister()`, `CustomMustRegister()`, and `Register()`.\n\n- **Metric Creation**: Metrics are created using Kubernetes' custom types (`metrics.NewCounter()`, `metrics.NewGauge()`, `metrics.NewHistogram()`) defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/counter.go`, `gauge.go`, and `histogram.go`. These wrappers extend Prometheus metrics with stability level tracking.\n\n- **Registration Pattern**: Metrics are registered using `legacyregistry.MustRegister()` for standard metrics or `legacyregistry.CustomMustRegister()` for custom collectors. The registry is initialized in `init()` with process and Go collectors.\n\n- **Key Files**:\n  - `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/legacyregistry/registry.go` - Global registry definition\n  - `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/counter.go` - Counter wrapper implementation\n  - `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/gauge.go` - Gauge wrapper implementation\n  - `staging/src/k8s.io/component-base/metrics/histogram.go` - Histogram wrapper implementation\n  - `pkg/controller/job/metrics/metrics.go` - Example registration using `Register()` with `sync.Once` guard\n  - `pkg/controller/nodelifecycle/metrics.go` - Example registration pattern\n\n### Grafana (grafana/grafana)\n\nGrafana uses the **standard Prometheus client library directly** with registration functions:\n\n- **Metric Creation**: Metrics are created using standard Prometheus functions (`prometheus.NewCounter()`, `prometheus.NewGauge()`, `prometheus.NewHistogram()` and their Vec variants).\n\n- **Registration Pattern**: Metric registration happens through dedicated registration functions that accept `prometheus.Registerer` as a parameter. These functions create the metrics and immediately register them with `registry.MustRegister()`. This pattern allows flexibility in using different registries.\n\n- **Key Files**:\n  - `pkg/infra/metrics/metrics.go` - Defines global metric variables but doesn't register them\n  - `pkg/registry/apis/provisioning/jobs/metrics.go` - Registration functions `RegisterJobMetrics()` and `RegisterQueueMetrics()` that take a registerer parameter\n  - `pkg/infra/httpclient/httpclientprovider/prometheus_metrics_middleware.go` - Example of `Register()` and `MustRegister()` methods that work with a provided registerer\n  - `pkg/registry/apis/provisioning/controller/metrics.go` - Registration function with metrics creation inside `registerFinalizerMetrics()`\n  - `pkg/services/auth/idimpl/metrics.go` - Pattern of checking `if reg != nil` before registering\n\n### Prometheus (prometheus/prometheus)\n\nPrometheus uses **constructor functions that return metrics structs** with explicit registration:\n\n- **Metric Creation and Registration**: Metrics are created with `prometheus.New*()` functions inside constructor functions (e.g., `newScrapeMetrics()`, `NewManagerMetrics()`) that take a `prometheus.Registerer` parameter.\n\n- **Registration Pattern**: Metrics are collected in a slice and registered in a loop with error handling. The function returns both the metrics struct and an error. This provides better control and error reporting compared to panic-on-error approaches.\n\n- **Unregistration Support**: Many metric structs include an `Unregister()` method to clean up metrics when they're no longer needed, demonstrating proper lifecycle management.\n\n- **Key Files**:\n  - `scrape/metrics.go` - `newScrapeMetrics()` function that creates and registers ~20 metrics with explicit error handling loop (lines 266-303)\n  - `discovery/metrics.go` - `NewManagerMetrics()` function demonstrating the pattern with metrics creation followed by registration loop and error handling\n  - `notifier/metric.go` - Metric creation and registration for alerting\n  - `storage/remote/queue_manager.go` - Metrics creation in constructor\n  - `tsdb/db.go` - Database metrics registration\n  - `tsdb/head.go` - Head metrics using `prometheus.NewGaugeFunc()` for dynamic values\n  - `rules/group.go` - Rule group metrics\n  - `discovery/kubernetes/metrics.go` - Kubernetes discovery metrics\n\n### Key Differences and Patterns\n\n1. **Registry Management**:\n   - Kubernetes: Central global registry with custom wrapper\n   - Grafana: Flexible registration with provided registerer parameter\n   - Prometheus: Constructor pattern with explicit error handling\n\n2. **Error Handling**:\n   - Kubernetes: Uses `MustRegister()` which panics on error\n   - Grafana: Uses `MustRegister()` or `Register()` with panic/error returns\n   - Prometheus: Explicit loop with error wrapping and return\n\n3. **Initialization Timing**:\n   - Kubernetes: Metrics created at package init time, registered separately via functions\n   - Grafana: Metrics created on demand when registration functions are called\n   - Prometheus: Both creation and registration happen in constructor functions\n\n4. **Unregistration Support**:\n   - Kubernetes: No explicit unregistration (global registry)\n   - Grafana: Limited unregistration support\n   - Prometheus: Explicit `Unregister()` methods for lifecycle management\n\nAll three projects use the same underlying Prometheus client library (`github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus`) but with different abstraction levels and registration strategies suited to their architectural needs."
}

